/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm (# The Unit Problem in Agent Systems) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm (**Status:** final conceptual/methods synthesis draft) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (**Date:** 2026-05-03) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm (**Theme:** agent-systems / evaluation-benchmarking / governance) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm (## Abstract) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (Recent work on agent systems has exposed at least four recurring failures in contemporary) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm (discourse: systems are evaluated at the wrong unit, properties are attributed to the wrong) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm (bearer, control is sought at the wrong layer, and governance is attached to the wrong) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (object. This paper argues that these are not four independent mistakes. They are four) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (manifestations of a deeper structural problem: repeated misidentification of the operative) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (unit in agent systems. As language models become embedded in workflows, tools, memory,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (permissions, runtime environments, and oversight structures, the base model increasingly) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (ceases to be a sufficient placeholder for the practical system. The deeper mistake is to let) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (one placeholder object perform too many analytic roles at once: measured unit, explanatory) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm (bearer, intervention target, and governed object. This paper synthesizes a four-paper) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (sequence on evaluation, attribution, control, and governance into a general argument about) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm (the unit problem in agent science. It explains why the relevant unit became unstable, shows) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (how unit confusion cascades across technical and institutional discourse, and proposes a) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm (unit-aware research discipline for studying deployed agent systems.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (## 1. Introduction) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (A large share of AI discourse still defaults to the model as its central object. A benchmark) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm (score is treated as if it described the model. A memory behavior is treated as if it) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm (belonged to the model. A refusal is treated as if it were a model property. A governance) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (claim is treated as if it attached to the model. In many cases this remains acceptable) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (shorthand. In a growing number of cases, it does not.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm (As agent systems become scaffolded, persistent, tool-using, and side-effect capable, the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (practical system being discussed often no longer coincides with the base model. The acting) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm (object is assembled from workflow structure, memory policy, permissioning, orchestration) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (logic, tool wrappers, budget ceilings, runtime boundaries, logging, and human oversight. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm (model remains central, but it is no longer a sufficient stand-in for the whole.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm (This paper argues that the field is therefore facing a broader **unit problem**. The problem) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm (is not merely that benchmarks are imperfect, or that attribution is sloppy, or that control) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm (and governance are underdeveloped. It is that the same placeholder object-usually the model-) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 182 Tm (is repeatedly asked to serve too many analytic roles at once.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 154 Tm (Those roles should be distinguished.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 140 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 126 Tm (- The **measured unit** is the object an evaluation actually tests.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 112 Tm (- The **explanatory bearer** is the object to which an observed property properly belongs.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 98 Tm (- The **intervention target** is the object through which practical leverage is best) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 84 Tm (exercised.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm (- The **governed object** is the object around which authority, oversight, and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 56 Tm (accountability should attach.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
