BT
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm (In simple systems these may coincide often enough that the distinction can be ignored. In) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm (deployed agent systems they increasingly do not. The real error is therefore not only) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (choosing the wrong unit once. It is pretending that one convenient placeholder can do all) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm (four jobs.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm (### 1.1 Contributions) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (This paper makes five contributions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm (1. It defines a general **unit problem** underlying recent confusion in agent discourse.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (2. It synthesizes evaluation, attribution, control, and governance as four linked symptoms) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (of that deeper problem.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (3. It explains why the model became an increasingly unstable default unit for deployed agent) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (systems.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (4. It shows how unit confusion cascades across technical and institutional reasoning.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (5. It proposes a more concrete discipline of **unit-aware agent science**.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (## 2. Why the Unit Became Unstable) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (The model-centered picture made more sense in an earlier regime of shorter-horizon) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm (interaction. If the practical object of interest was largely prompt-response generation,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (then the model itself could plausibly anchor measurement, explanation, intervention, and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (policy.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (That picture eroded as systems acquired:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm (- persistent or semi-persistent memory,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (- workflow decomposition,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (- tool access,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm (- retry and checkpoint logic,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm (- budget constraints,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (- approval gates,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm (- runtime policies,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (- logging and trace retention,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm (- and human supervisors with intervention rights.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm (These additions are not secondary cosmetics. They partly determine what the system can do,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm (what it can remember, how it can be interrupted, and how its actions can be reconstructed) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm (after the fact. Once those layers materially shape practical behavior, the base model stops) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 182 Tm (being a universally adequate placeholder.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 154 Tm (The resulting instability is important for a second reason. It does not simply replace one) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 140 Tm (unit with another in a clean once-and-for-all way. Different analytic tasks can now point to) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 126 Tm (different relevant units. What is being measured may be a workflow-conditioned system. What) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 112 Tm (explains a property may be a harness-memory composite. What offers the best intervention) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 98 Tm (point may be permissions or orchestration. What ought to be governed may be the full action) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 84 Tm (system. There is therefore no single permanent replacement unit that solves every problem.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm (The real shift is that unit selection has become task-dependent and must be declared rather) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 56 Tm (than assumed.) Tj
ET
endstream
