/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm (and governable field.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm (## 9. Limitations) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm (This paper is a conceptual synthesis rather than a new empirical study. Its value depends on) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm (whether the four-way distinction it organizes proves useful in later experimental and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm (institutional work.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (There is also a risk of overextension. Not every system requires a fully widened unit) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm (analysis, and in some settings the model will remain the correct dominant object.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (A second limitation is boundary ambiguity. As systems become sociotechnical, it can be) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (contested where the relevant unit begins and ends.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (Finally, the paper does not offer a fully formal theory of units in agent systems. Its aim) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (is more modest: to identify a recurrent structural error, clarify its variants, and push the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (field toward better object-discipline.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (## 10. Conclusion) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (The field's current difficulties with agent systems are often narrated as separate problems:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm (weak evaluation, sloppy attribution, misplaced control, and underdeveloped governance. This) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (paper argued that they are better understood as four symptoms of one deeper structural) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (failure.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (The failure is repeated misidentification of the operative unit.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm (As language models become embedded in workflows, memory, tools, permissions, environments,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (and oversight structures, the model increasingly ceases to be a sufficient placeholder for) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (the acting system. Yet discourse continues to rely on it as if it were simultaneously the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm (unit of measurement, explanation, intervention, and governance.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (That habit is no longer just imprecise. It is becoming an obstacle to agent science itself.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm (It compresses away the structure that users depend on, obscures where properties belong,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (mislocates intervention leverage, and hides where authority actually lives.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm (If the field learns to identify the relevant unit more carefully, a better path opens: more) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm (cumulative comparisons, more accurate explanations, more realistic control, and more honest) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm (governance. If it does not, it will continue to speak clearly about the wrong object-and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm (then build methods, institutions, and policies around that mistake.) Tj
ET
endstream
